phrases: Honestly, I was not going to play volleyball in high school.
Sports have always been the only thing I was good at.
I would get better records in track or swimming than kids on the teams.
I would end up qualifying for meets.
I earned a lot of resentment.
I just liked moving my body.
But the harder I tried, the more I hurt people.
Even on the volleyball team I joined in junior high,
everyone acted like that was expected.
Kaizaki-kun, you asked me the other day
why I did not go to a school with a better volleyball team.
I just got sick of it in junior high,
so I turned down offers from all powerhouse teams.
But I still wanted to play something,
so I came to check out the volleyball team, hoping against hope.
And that is where I met Rena.
Okay, trial first-years, that is enough.
We are still going tomorrow, so come hang out, if you like.
This is a prep school that does not care about sports too much.
If I play well, I will find good teammates to play volleyball with.
You are Tamarai-san from Toyofuji Junior High, right?
What the hell were you doing today?
You do not need to work any harder at Aoba, huh?
If you hold back, I will be pissed.
I actually hit it with everything I had!
I knew you were holding back!
You will join the team, right, Tamarai Honoka-san?
For the next three years, I am going to practice real hard
and get good enough to match you.
Do not you dare hold back again.
It was my first time having a rival.
If it were not for Rena, I would not have gotten to spend three wonderful years here.
I am really grateful to her.
That is why I want to play our last match together.
But Rena said she could not.
I am scared we will not even be friends anymore.
I want to talk to her...
But she might push me away again.
I am afraid the next time I speak to her really will be the last.
I transferred a lot as a kid.
I would make friends, and then transfer again.
I could feel my heart growing numb.
Was there any point to me being there?
I grew convinced that no one would even remember me.
I gave up on knowing people.
And this mess is the result.
If you keep avoiding her, you will drift further apart,
and you really will not know how to talk to them.
Do not give up like I did.
The bond between you two makes me...
The bond between you makes me very jealous.
The times you are spending now, and the friends you have,
Make the most of them, or you will regret it someday.
I will go talk to Rena.
I cannot leave things like this.
You have not smiled like that in a while.
You were quite ugly the other day.
Ah, sorry we kept you this long.
I really want to play in the tournament with you.
I do not want things to end like this.
It is my fault you got hurt, so maybe I am being selfish.
I am done with the team!
I am going to watch the tournament.
I want to see what you two always looked so happy talking about.
I do not know if I should say this,
but Kariu was crying the other day.
The day after she got hurt, I think.
Back then, I had no idea why she was crying.
But I think I get it now.
If she really did not care about you or the club,
I do not think she would cry.
So, um, I do not know how to say it...
My point is, what she said just now is not how she really feels.
I am going to trust her and wait.
Sorry I could not be of more help.
I was only able to talk to Tamarai-san because you were there.
Tamarai-san said she would trust Kariu-san and wait.
Again, why use that sticker there?!
I was wondering about your schedule this weekend.
Going to watch volleyball with Hishiro-san.
I just felt like saying thanks.
You are not making any sense.
Well, I will see you tomorrow.
Let us have a good match!
I knew she would not show.
But the tournament goes on tomorrow, too!
If they lose, they do not play ever again, let alone tomorrow.
Does anybody know where Kariu lives?
I will drag her here if I have to.
Do you know where she lives?
It is bad enough that he knows her address,
but to send it with this timing is really creepy!
Oga, keep us updated on the match.
Not like you to step in and help.
You are always yelling at me for getting too involved.
Are you that happy things are changing?
She might not open if she knows it is us.
Lying comes as naturally to you as breathing.
Did you really have to go that far?
We have come too far to let you get away, Kariu.
We all believed you would come and waited, but you did not.
So we came to drag you there.
I never asked you to believe in me.
I did not want to go, so I did not.
Do not show up like this.
You are dressed like you are going.
You wanted to go, did not you?
To play one last match with Tamarai-san.
It is none of your business.
You have got a lot of nerve.
Hishiro, you are too dense to understand how I feel, so stop trying!
If I do not understand how a friend feels,
am I not allowed to worry about them?
If I do not experience what you do,
am I not allowed to worry about you, my friend?
Please, let that iron guard down for a minute.
I know, when you have hit rock bottom,
people trying to cheer you up can be really annoying.
But what if someone you are pushing away
Hishiro may be awkward, but she was genuinely worried.
I did not ask her to be.
Knock it off already, you stubborn fool.
To throw away three years of practice like this?
To cut ties with your best friend?
To spend the rest of the school year all alone?
You cannot come back to it.
I want you to go to that match and laugh with Tamarai-san again.
I want the three of us to eat lunch together again.
I am not trying to patronize you.
Just trying to fulfill my selfish desire.
Do you really want things to stay this way?
We all worked so hard, and this is the last...
But I have not practiced for two weeks.
I cannot stand next to Honoka.
My teammates will not want me there.
I cannot just jump into a match
So I made up my mind to quit and left the team.
I could not back down from that
and said some horrible things, so why are you all being so nice to me?
You will not let me give up!
Tamarai-san said she wants to play with you, too.
But since she caused your sprain, she could not bring herself
to ask you to grant her selfish desire.
There is no problem at all.
I mean, you both want to play your last game together,
and we all want you to.
All of our selfish desires align.
Will you run if I do not drag you?
They are on the back foot.
We could not play well without you!
So we can all play together longer!
Why did I sit between them?
I kept thinking I had to keep it together, but I could not.
But when you came, I really wanted to win, and rushed things.
Would you have won without me?
You should have seen the look on my face when you were not here!
Even if we had won like that, I would not have been happy.
It would not have been fun.
We lost, but that match was super fun.
Honoka, were you going to Aoba College?
Then we are not done yet.
Let us play volleyball again in college!
Sorry I was so mean the day I got hurt.
Thanks for not giving up on me.
No, I am sorry for causing your sprain.
It is all thanks to you, Hishiro!
Hishiro's doing that creepy smile again!
But it is a super weird smile!
All's well that ends well, huh?
We would never seen Tama-chan look so alive during a match, either!
We have got to keep score!
Is that a new hair tie, Rena?
Oh, I forgot I borrowed it from Hishiro.
Come to think of it, Hishiron's always wearing the same ones, huh?
